abstract: Trustbusting advocates like Sarah Miller, who target corporate power, have finally found themselves at the center of the political conversation.
snippet: Trustbusting advocates like Sarah Miller, who target corporate power, have finally found themselves at the center of the political conversation.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — One night five years ago, Sarah Miller, a former Treasury Department aide, was trying to make sense of an economic recovery that had left the country in the grips of rising inequality.

headline_main: What’s at Stake in the New Hampshire Primary
byline_original: By Reid J. Epstein and Adriana Ramić

abstract: The candidate keeps talking about winning “unwinnable fights.” But the New Hampshire primary was not supposed to be in that category.
snippet: The candidate keeps talking about winning “unwinnable fights.” But the New Hampshire primary was not supposed to be in that category.
lead_paragraph: CONCORD, N.H. — Two days before a once-mission-critical primary in a state she neighbors, Senator Elizabeth Warren — typically exceptional at holding a room — had not finished speaking when something unusual happened: Dozens of voters began filtering out of the middle school gym she had reserved.

abstract: The “first in the nation” primary never lets Iowa tell it what to do. Especially not this year.
snippet: The “first in the nation” primary never lets Iowa tell it what to do. Especially not this year.
lead_paragraph: DERRY, N.H. — Throughout the nearly half century-long presidential rivalry between Iowa and New Hampshire, sometimes a state has to dig deep to make its case for why its contest is in fact superior.

abstract: A new series from Ava DuVernay debuts on OWN, while a legal drama arrives on ABC.
snippet: A new series from Ava DuVernay debuts on OWN, while a legal drama arrives on ABC.
lead_paragraph: CHERISH THE DAY 10 p.m. on OWN. After creating the OWN family drama “Queen Sugar,” Ava DuVernay was invited to bring another show to the network. The result is this new anthology series. The season follows the relationship of a single couple, each episode focusing on a momentous, single day they share together. The premiere stars Xosha Roquemore (“The Mindy Project”) and Alano Miller (“Underground”) as a couple in Los Angeles who, over the course of several years, forge a deep connection and face hurdles that challenge their relationship.
